article.headline: Chattanooga 75, Furman 59
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Chris Early scored 23 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Chattanooga over Furman 75-59 on Monday night, ending a four-game skid for the Mocs. Omar Wattad and Keegan Bell each added 14 points and Ricky Taylor had 11 for the Mocs (15-14, 11-5 Southern Conference), who remained in a tie atop the conference's North division with Western Carolina. The Catamounts defeated North Carolina-Greensboro 70-66 on Monday night. Chattanooga led 38-26 at halftime and extended that lead to as many as 23, 63-40, following a 14-2 run over a 3:20 span in the second half. The Paladins (20-8, 12-5) attempted a season-high 32 shots from 3-point range, but connected on only 21.9 percent of those attempts (7 of 32) -- their second-lowest percentage of the season. Noah States scored 20 points on 8-of-10 shooting and Amu Saaka added 10 for Furman.
